==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Abduct
<hw>Ab*duct"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Abducted</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Abducting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>abductus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>abducere</ets>. See
<er>Abduce</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To take away surreptitiously by
force; to carry away (a human being) wrongfully and usually by violence;
to kidnap.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To draw away, as a limb or other part, from its
ordinary position.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>abducting</ent>⟦br⟧
